This paper is about machine learning and data mining, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on vector quantization, which is a technique used in many areas of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), and data science (cs.DS) more broadly. The paper also discusses the acceleration of approximate vector operations, which is relevant to databases (cs.DB). Given these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.DS, and cs.DB.
